 a factor\nof $\\sim 3$ systematic uncertainty. The scatter in ${\\epsilon}_{\\rm ff}$ from\ncloud to cloud within the Milky Way is a factor of a few. We conclude that\n$L_{\\rm HCN}$ is an effective tracer of dense gas and that the IR$-$HCN\ncorrelation is a significant diagnostic of the microphysics of star formation\nin dense gas.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 30 Jan 2018 12:26:11 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 31 Jan 2018 22:14:44 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Tue, 11 Sep 2018 08:54:38 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-09-12"}
